    div.glossary-entry(data-entry="aracha")
      header
        h3 Aracha
      section
        section
          p Aracha is a very basic tea. It basically contains all the parts of the Camellia Sinensis, that can be used to create Tea. So this tea consists of: Leaves, Leaf Stalk, Stems, Leaf Hair as well as broken Leaves. All these ingredients are steamed and rolled.

          p Usually Aracha is beeing finished after it has been sold, which means that Aracha is mainy as basis for other Green Teas to build upon. Aracha is for example used to blend different Flavorprofiles of Sencha.

    div.glossary-entry(data-entry="gyokuro")
      header
        h3 Gyokuro, »Jewel Dew«

      section
        section
          p Gyokuro is one of most high quality Teas Japan has to offer. Of course also within this type of Tea there are different stages of quality. This type of Tea grows for 21 days in the shade before beeing harvested. Gyokuro is grown on a special variety of the Camellia Sinensis, such as Asahi, Okumidori, Yamakai, and Saemidori. This Tea is in need of special care, when prepared. The name »Jewel Dew« refers to the pale green color of the Tea.

