    div.glossary-entry(data-entry="kukicha")
      header
        h3 Kukicha

      section
        section
          p Kukicha is a japenese Green Tea, which mainly consists of Leaf Veins and Stems, and therefore also contains less theine. The quality of Kukicha is similar to the quality of Sencha.

          p If Kukicha consist of Leaf Vains that were during the preparation of Gyokuro, it is called Karigane or Shiarore to indicate the special taste.

