    div.glossary-entry(data-entry="kamairicha")
      header
        h3 Kamairicha

      section
        section
          p Kamairicha is very different from other Japanese Teas. In fact this Tea doesn't even fit the typical flavor profile of Japenese Green Tea. Very early in the process of creating this Tea, the Leaves are roasted at about&nbsp;
            span.no-break ~ 300 °C
            | . These Leaves are not steamed. Typically this Tea is shaped into comma or Magatama. The shape of the processed Tea Leaves reminds more of Chinese Teas than Japanese.

          p This Tea is said have a slightly roasted flavor and fresh sweetness.

